com.vectorprint.report.itext.style

Class FontLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vectorprint.report.itext.style.FontLoader

  • public class FontLoader
extends Object
    support for loading of iText and awt fonts, also from URL or stream, note that you have to call setLoadAWTFonts(boolean) and / or setLoadiText(boolean) to load any fonts. By default uses embedding of fonts.
    Author:
    Eduard Drenth: VectorPrint

      • loadFont

        public FontLoader.LOADSTATUS loadFont(String path)
                               throws com.vectorprint.VectorPrintException
        Bottleneck method for loading fonts, calls FontFactory.register(java.lang.String) for iText, GraphicsEnvironment.registerFont(java.awt.Font) for awt.
        Parameters:
        path - the path to the font file
        family - will always be converted to lower case
        reload - when false and FontFactory.isRegistered(java.lang.String) returns true, iText fonts will not be reloaded
        Returns:
        Throws:
        com.vectorprint.VectorPrintException
